        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:04PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 404 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 14 miles southwest of Torreon to over
Los Lunas, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albuquerque, Rio Rancho, Los Lunas, Bernalillo, Valencia,
Corrales, Los Ranchos De Albuquerque, Bosque Farms, Tijeras and
Paradise Hills.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 135 and 182.
Highway 550 between Mile Markers 1 and 11.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 199 and 244.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
